Permit to Carry (Concealed Carry*) Class in Winona, August 16th at 9am. The class will be held at the Winona Sportsmen's Club.

or text/call REDACTED

Why should you get a Permit to Carry?

You should get one so that you can defend yourself and loved ones from the numerous "bad guys" out there that prey on the law abiding citizens. Most violent encounters are over within a minute and the typical police response is greater than 5 minutes. Some people believe that the only people that get a Permit to Carry are "gun nuts" or "wanna be cops" That is far from the truth. People who get their Permit to Carry are regular people that want to be able to take responsibility for their own safety and security. They are Doctors, Lawyers, blue collar workers, bankers, computer programmers, accountants, retirees and housewives.
Gun Ownership is a serious responsibility and the use of deadly force is a very serious matter and so is protecting yourself and loved ones. Do you know what Minnesota's Use of Force Laws are? Even if you do not want to get your Permit to Carry or even carry a firearm, you should still get training in the safe handling of firearms and the laws of self-defense.

If you need a gun for the shooting portion of the class I will have guns available for free. 

This class is good for the Minnesota Permit to Carry and also Florida, Arizona, Maine, Idaho, Kansas, Oklahoma, Iowa, Wisconsin and Michigan Non resident permits.
With the Minnesota Permit to Carry you are legal to carry in up to 23 States. With the Non-Resident Permits you could get up to 35 states.

title: For Sale:  Ruger 10/22 Integrally Suppressed
postcontent:
Anson Tactical Arms is a licensed Manufacturer and Dealer in Firearms and NFA items. Suppressors (Silencers) are legal to own in North Carolina with the proper paperwork.  No credit card fees! Use the contact button or call / text REDACTED. If you use the email option, please check your spam folder. We typically respond in 12 hours or less.  Free shipping to your class 2 or 3 dealer.  NC Residents add 6.75% sales tax.

Ruger 10/22 Integrally suppressed with Houge over molded stock.  Black stock is shown, but we have most other colors in stock as well.  This rifle is very quiet.  The integrally suppressed barrel has ports to allow you to shoot cheap bulk pack high velocity ammo at subsonic speeds, eliminating the sonic crack.  This means you get a super quiet rifle without having to buy expensive subsonic ammo.  You can close these ports, and the ammo will remain supersonic.  This must transfer to an individual or trust on a form 4 or dealer on a form 3.  If you are not familiar with this process we can help.

Specs on the barrel:

Fusion T22. The convergence of quiet and short.

Want to quiet your 10/22 in the shortest possible package with only a single tax stamp? The Huntertown Arms Fusion T22 is a short, light, and quiet bull barrel replacement for your 10/22. At just 16.5 inches long, you will have the perfect plinking, target, or hunting rifle.

Upgrades

Need a new barrel in your integral suppressor? Want to change the twist rate? What about moving it to a different host weapon? Unlike most integral suppressors on the market today that register the barrel as the suppressor and use some type of baffle insert, the Fusion T22 has a suppressor tube and the barrel is the baffle stack. If there is an issue with the barrel for any reason, we can repair or replace it. Can you do this with any other integral barrel?

The Fusion T22 has a ported barrel to slow bulk pack ammo to subsonic speeds. But we didn't stop there. You have the option to open and close the ports, allowing you to decide whether to fire at subsonic or supersonic speeds.

Material

The Fusion T22 is constructed entirely of stainless steel and is a direct replacement for the Ruger 10/22 bull barrel. 	Specifications

Supported Calibers: 	.22LR

title: For Sale:  LWRC M6A2 SPR Mod 0 with AAC 51T flash hider
postcontent:
The new LWRC International Special Purpose Rifle (SPR) is the epitome of a well-balanced and fast pointing tactical carbine. The rifle uses a lightweight sculpted rail derived from our REPR platform. The SPR-MOD rail, at 12” in length, is 33% longer than our Mark II-B rail, but incredibly is still 5% lighter. The cold hammer forged barrel is spiral fluted prior to being treated with our NiCorr surface conversion process. The spiral fluting shaves 20% of the weight off the barrel and relieves the longitudinal stresses that can cause the stringing seen in conventionally fluted barrels. The weight reduction in the front end and the svelte wrist of the user configurable rail, make for an incredibly well balanced rifle.

The SPR features our enhanced fire control group. The fire control group and the bolt carrier are coated in our proprietary nickel coating that promotes permanent lubricity and allows the operator to run the gun nearly dry when the situation requires it. The piston system is our mid-length system, which provides a more direct recoil impulse for faster follow-up shots.

The ACOG is not for sale.  The Surefire M952V can be purchased seperately for $175.

FAQ - PLEASE READ! I am not going to respond to questions that are covered here!

Q. I am interested in your gun. Is it still available?
A. If you see this ad, most likely. The firearms are reserved for pickup on my web site, by making an appointment to buy. Someone could be doing it right now, and first person to reserve the firearm wins. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment on the site. If someone has made it just before you, I will notify you within a short time (usually, an hour), otherwise - see you shortly.

PLEASE DO NOT ASK WHETHER THE GUN IS STILL AVAILABLE! I WILL NOT RESPOND.

Q. How do I buy?
A. This is a dealer listing, NICS check, taxes, etc are all required. Please go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick up.

Q. I am interested in your gun. Call me @ xxx-xxx-xxxx
A. Excellent. Go to www.preciseshooter.com -> FAQ -> How to buy, read the requirements, and make the appointment to pick it up.

Q. Are there any other fees, in addition to the price and taxes? NICS, background check, etc?
A. No.

Q. What is the tax rate?
A. 9.5%

Q. Where are you located?
A. Queen Anne neighborhood in Seattle.

Q. Can we meet in Burien on Monday morning?
A. No, FFL requirements are that the transfers happen at a licensed location. Also, the only times you can come over are the appointments that you can reserve on the site. No other time slots are available.

Q. I see you carry Savage rifles. Can you find me MKII FV-SR?
A. No. Please see here for what I can or cannot do: http://www.preciseshooter.com/NotInStock.aspx

Q. Do you take trades?
A. Sometimes. However:
a) firearms only,
b) they need to be our of current production (I can get new ones at wholesale prices), or you have to offer them to me at well below wholesale
c) I do not resell the trades, so they should fit my personal interests (which only include military as well as highly accurate, competition guns - no self defense guns like Glocks, M&Ps, XD*, and the like)
d) the exchange rate should be fair (see here for more: http://www.preciseshooter.com/blog/PriceGuide.aspx

Q. Is the price firm? Will you take XXX (70% of the asking price)?
A. The price is firm.

Q. Can you help me mount a scope/replace a trigger/fix a feeding problem?
A. Sorry, I do not do gunsmithing.

Q. Will you ship?
A. Yes - go to www.preciseshooter.com -> How to buy and read the section for buying outside Seattle area. Shipping by insured Priority Mail is $25.

title: For Sale:  Sig P229R .40 - 9 mags - 3 holsters
postcontent:
This is a great package for a new gun to CCW

For sale is a used Sig P229R (purchased in 2007) in .40 S&W. This is a NON E2 model with a short extractor and original mainspring and strut. This handgun is DA/SA, and I have swapped out the factory hollow aluminum guide rod with a Bedair stainless guide rod. This adds a tiny amount of weight to the front, so it helps slightly with recoil and is a bit stronger than the factory guide rod - but is mainly just more attractive than the original one. I do also have the factory blue box the gun originally came in.

I also am including 9 standard capacity magazines for the handgun. They are .40/.357Sig 12rd magazines, and each one of them has a brand new Wolff extra strength spring in them.

The three holsters included are:

1 High Noon Custom - Slide Guard (with lining) OWB cowhide holster. This is a custom made high ride holster with belt loops that fit up to 1 3/4" belts. It has an adjustable tension screw to fine tune the strength of the retention on the holster. If you have never experienced a custom leather holster - it is AMAZING! Mass produced holsters do not have the detailed boning that custom holsters have which does not retain the handgun as well as custom holsters. If you have ever experienced a mass produced leather holster, you know that the leather becomes well-worked and soft within a month or so, but you don't have any of that with the High Noon. It will be just as rigid as it was when it was made forever.

The second holster is a Bianchi IWB concealment holster. I have carried the Sig in an "appendix carry" position as well as 3:30-4:00 and it works very well.

The third and final holster is a great range holster. It is the very popular Blackhawk Serpa holster. It includes both the belt attachment and the quick attach pancake attachment.

If you need ammo I can also make you a deal on Federal HST for CCW - but ammunition is NOT included in the asking price for this listing.

Most agree that the Makarov produced by East Germany is the finest ever made. Fit and finish is certainly superior to the Russian & Bulgarians I've seen. The bluing is deep and dark with a high polish that looks like what you'd find on a high end Colt, but certainly not on a military pistol.  

Action is smooth and tolerances are tight. I'd rate this pistol at a conservative 95%. There is little wear and the bore is absolutely mirror bright. It was made in 1962 and all numbers match except for the mags which are not factory numbered.

Original E. German brown leather holster in excellent shape with a correct Makarov (screwdriver tip) cleaning rod.  

Four original E. German magazines all in very good or better condition.  

Correct E. German black rope lanyard.  

A spare set of real Russian Red Star thumb rest grips with lanyard loop, screw & Russian leather lanyard. (in case you want to dress it up to look like a Russian).  

 Federal Arms stainless steel threaded barrel in .380ACP. These are very hard to find today and this one is new/unfired in original packaging.  

A SIONICS style FAKE suppressor in blue steel that's designed to work with the threaded Federal barrel. This will look "super bad" when installed.  

250 rounds of fresh SILVER BEAR 9x18 ammo. Zinc plated steel cases, 94 grain FMJ bullets, non-corrosive. Great target & blasting ammo.

title: For Sale:  600 Rounds Federal HST .40S&W JHP - Preferred Police Ammo
postcontent:
For sale is 600 rounds of Federal HST 155gr JHP for a .40S&W. Federal released its Hydra-Shok line of ammunition to capture the law enforcement market years ago, and while it was a good round - it proved troublesome when going through barriers before reaching its target - clogging much of the time.

Federal corrected the problem by introducing a line known as HST, and it was tested extensively by the FBI upon its release in .40 caliber, and adopted as their ammunition after blowing the tests out of the water. This is currently the only ammunition I will carry as I feel like it is the only ammunition to hold a candle to the famous "Black Talon". 

It's easy to find the much less desirable Hydra-Shok ammunition on the shelf, and many people are intrigued by the "post" inside the hollow point. If you do the research, and I suggest you do, you will find that HST is extremely tough to beat. 

That's why HST has almost never (in my experience) been for sale on the shelves at your local gun shop - I have only ever found it online, for a premium price, and in small or limited quantities. I have recently switched to a different caliber for my preferred CCW and cannot find anywhere that sells HST in bulk, must less a place with a single box in stock right now. 

I live in Puyallup, but will be willing to drive a reasonable distance to meet - or even ship if you want to pay for shipping. 

Take a look here for FBI Protocol test results on this ammunition
http://le.atk.com/ammunition/federal/handgun/details.aspx?id=567
